{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that was still early, but actually it was still far off because I was talking about how the life at Koper's.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And basically, what happened there is that we were very well informed because there was-- there were the underground newspapers, and that were, of course, German newspapers and the Polish-- official Polish newspaper.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we knew about the progress of the front and the fact that the Germans are-- at least in our eyes, we're certain that the Germans were losing the war, and that, particularly, the Russians are coming near.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we knew as well other thing because there was a book, or at least-- yes, a book published in probably Warsaw during the war called or written by somebody called [INAUDIBLE], which he described in the greatest detail everything that happened in Treblinka and how the people, Warsaw Jews, were killed, and all the details, including the gas chambers and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we knew all that already.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think probably it was in 1944, because this chap escaped-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] should I look at--",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It will take time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I better answer it I think.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's better.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we knew everything about what was happening this time in great detail.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were staying at Koper's, although it was-- we knew that it was terribly dangerous.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we had no other-- there was no escape for us because we had no money anymore, and there was no other possibility.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But actually, there were some people who left Koper on occasion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a lawyer there, Goldstein, who lived with us at Koper, as well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But on one occasion, he said Koper had belonged to the underground organization, and we gestapo arrested somebody in this underground organization.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
